					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of works in Lurianic kabbalah.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="">
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḳovets be-ḳabalat ha-Ar"i</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">קובץ בקבלת האר"י</title>
							<locus from="1r" to="223v"/>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="2r" to="126v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-gilgulim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר הגלגולים</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">Vital, Ḥayyim ben Joseph, 1542-1620</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">ויטל, חיים בן יוסף</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>See <ref target="Avivi_2008" type="page">708-710</ref>, vol. 2.</p>
								<p>The volume contains 73 chapters, redacted by Nathan ben Reuven Shapira, with his comments, and additional glosses by Benyamin ha-Cohen, Moses ben Mordecai Zacuto, Jacob Zemah and others.</p>
								<p>Includes: a commentary on Saba de-mishpatim concerning metempsychosis (folio 110r) and a piece on the same subject, ascribed to Israel Sarug and transmitted by Menahem Azariah of Fano (folio 112r). Folios 123v-126v contain an index of gilgulim.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="127r" to="162v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Peri ῾ets ḥayim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרי עץ חיים </title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">Vital, Ḥayyim ben Joseph, 1542-1620</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">ויטל, חיים בן יוסף</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Contains only part four of the treatise, Sha῾ar ruaḥ ha-ḳodesh and Sha῾ar ha-nevu᾿ah, and parts of Sefer ha-yiḥudim (beginning on folio 139r).</p>
								<p>Folio 127r-127v: a tabulation of prophetic powers by Nathan ben Reuven Shapira.</p>
								<p>Includes comments by Moses ben Mordecai Zacuto.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="163r" to="204r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Torat Natan (liḳutim)</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תורת נתן (לקוטים)</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/66342902">Shapira, Natan ben Reuven</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/66342902">שפירא, נתן בן ראובן דוד</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Contains only some excerpts of the work, with additions in the margin. A short commentary on the passages of Mishna begins on folio 172v.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="204v" to="223r"/>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/23282531">Fano, Menahem Azariah da 1548-1620</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/23282531">מנחם עזריה מפנו</persName>
							</author>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">Vital, Ḥayyim ben Joseph, 1542-1620</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">ויטל, חיים בן יוסף</persName>
							</author>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Liḳutim mi-kitve Menaḥem Azariah mi-Fano</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">לקוטים מכתבי מנחם עזריה מפנו</title>
							<note>
								<p>Contains fragments of works of Ḥayim Vital and Menahem Azariah of Fano, with glosses by Nathan ben Reuven Shapira, perhaps the editor of this collection. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
